---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import ExternalLink from "../components/ExternalLink.astro";
import NewsletterButton from "../components/NewsletterButton.astro";
import NewsletterMediaSection from "../components/NewsletterMediaSection.astro";
import NewsletterSocialLinks from "../components/NewsletterSocialLinks.astro";
import {
  auraLink,
  instagramSection,
  movementLink,
  movementProducts,
  newsletterAssets,
  newsletterBackPath,
  newsletterSocialLinks,
  tipsLink,
  toolsLink,
  twitterSection,
} from "../data/newsletter";
import NewsletterLayout from "../layouts/NewsletterLayout.astro";
---

<NewsletterLayout
  title="Your Mental Moment - Sebastian Bogdan"
  description="Discover a sample newsletter Sebastian Bogdan designed, wrote, and sent out to thousands of subscribers at How Mental, called 'Your Mental Moment'."
  pathname="/your-mental-moment"
>
  <header role="banner" class="py-2">
    <p class="font-sans">
      Go <a href={newsletterBackPath} class="hover:text-teal underline">back</a>
    </p>
  </header>
  <main role="main">
    <div class="w-full bg-[#040404]">
      <Image
        src={newsletterAssets.howMentalDark}
        alt="How Mental logo"
        class="mx-auto w-[260px] py-4"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="bg-[#F40ACB] py-12 text-2xl leading-tight text-white">
      <p class="tracking-tight">Hey Sebastian!</p>
      <p class="font-black tracking-tight">This is Your Mental Moment 🧠🎉</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center bg-[#F0F0F0] py-5">
      <div class="mx-4 rounded-xl bg-white p-8 sm:w-[580px]">
        <p>
          These emails are packed full of mental goodness, use them to:<br /><br
          />1. Check in on your mind 🤙<br />
          2. Help the people around you 🧑‍🤝‍🧑<br />
          3. Get involved in The Mental Movement! 🌍❤️🧠<br /><br />We hope you
          enjoy what we drop in ya inbox and your day is a shade brighter with
          us. :)<br /><br />Love,<br /><br />George, Founder of How Mental
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center bg-[#F3FDF0] py-5">
      <Image
        src={newsletterAssets.mentalTips}
        alt="Mental Tips"
        class="px-4 sm:px-0"
        loading="eager"
      />
      <div class="mx-4 my-5 rounded-xl bg-white p-8 sm:w-[580px]">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold">This Week's Mental Tip: LIFE STAGES 🧑‍🎤</p>
        <br />
        <p>
          Recently I feel like I've entered a new stage of life. And, I started
          to think...wtf is a stage of life?! Does that lens really help me when
          I know I'm growing continuously? 🤔<br /><br />It's easy for me to
          look back on my existence and say "oh, that's when I was friends with
          X, or when I was doing Y job or when I was going through LMNOP",
          y'know what I mean?<br /><br />That emo stage...that was REAL (yep, I
          had one too 🙄) but it's also more than that. The people around me at
          that stage of life were soooo different to the people I have in my
          circle of friends now. We crossed for that moment and now we're in
          different stages. 💁‍♀️<br /><br />When depression massively took over my
          life for a year, I lost a lot. A lot of friends, a relationship, my
          sanity. It was really fucking hard. And all I wanted back then was for
          those people to stay, but that didn't happen. I was "too much" for
          them to handle. And I just had to accept it... 😔<br /><br />The idea
          of life stages made accepting losing those relationships easier. We
          were at different stages, and they went down a different path, one
          that doesn't include me. I can't beg people to stay in my life - and I
          don't need to - I just have to move onto the next stage, with more
          compatible friends.<br /><br />Still, losing people fucking sucks.
          Change is HARD! There's no particular stage we need to get to. But
          knowing and accepting our own stage can make things easier for us and
          a LOT more pleasurable. So let it happen, my love. Don't beat yourself
          up over the past, or the future. Love the stage you're at! 😘❤️
        </p>
      </div>
      <NewsletterButton link={tipsLink} />
    </div>
    <NewsletterMediaSection section={instagramSection} />
    <NewsletterMediaSection section={twitterSection} />
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center bg-[#FFF9EB] py-5">
      <Image
        src={newsletterAssets.mentalMovement}
        alt="Mental Movement"
        class="px-4 sm:px-0"
      />
      <div class="mx-4 my-5 rounded-xl bg-white p-8 sm:w-[580px]">
        <p class="font-bold">
          I don't know about you, but I'm DONE living in a world where wellbeing
          isn't a priority. <span class="text-[#FDB21C]">Mental Clothes</span>
          let people know you represent the need for change.
        </p>
        <br />
        <p>
          If you love our mission to make mental health a global priority and
          want to help us start more conversations about it, join us by repping
          The Mental Movement!<br /><br />And you'll look gooood whilst you're
          doing it! 😉
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mx-4 mb-6 flex flex-col gap-5 sm:w-[580px] sm:flex-row">
        {
          movementProducts.map((product) => (
            <div class="sm:w-1/2">
              <ExternalLink href={product.href}>
                <Image src={product.image} alt={product.alt} />
              </ExternalLink>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
      <NewsletterButton link={movementLink} />
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center bg-[#FEE9F9] py-5">
      <Image
        src={newsletterAssets.mentalTools}
        alt="Mental Tools"
        class="px-4 sm:px-0"
      />
      <div class="mx-4 my-5 sm:w-[580px]">
        <ExternalLink href="https://www.howmental.com/item/aura">
          <Image src={newsletterAssets.aura} alt="Aura logo" />
        </ExternalLink>
        <div class="rounded-b-xl bg-white px-8 py-6">
          <p class="font-bold">
            Is it just me or has EVERYTHING been draining recently?? I've had
            some awful sleep, and it feels like there isn't enough coffee in the
            WORLD to get me out of it...
          </p>
          <br />
          <p>
            And I'm starting to think that coffee might be the problem 😅 I
            don't think I've been taking care of my body enough, and maybe
            that's what's making me feel this way? 🤷‍♂️ I mean, I said this to my
            therapist and they nodded their head a lot more than they usually
            do... 🤔<br /><br />So I looked into it, and found Aura. YES, they
            do mindfulness - but nobody does it better! There's a reason they've
            been called the Spotify of Mindfulness and that's because they've
            got loadssss of coaches and professionals giving all the energy we
            need to stay in tune, get focused and live with a little zen! 😇<br
            /><br />Feel like chugging coffee isn't the way you wanna live? Try
            this!<br />👇👇👇
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <NewsletterButton link={auraLink} />
      <div class="mx-4 my-5 flex flex-col items-center sm:w-[580px]">
        <ExternalLink href="https://www.howmental.com/all/apps-products">
          <Image src={newsletterAssets.howMentalLight} alt="How Mental logo" />
        </ExternalLink>
        <div class="rounded-b-xl bg-white px-8 pb-6">
          <p class="font-bold">
            Not interested in Aura? We've got a whole universe of tools for you
            to try!
          </p>
          <br />
          <p>
            How Mental bridges the gap between you and all the Mental Tools,
            Knowledge & Community you need to stay sane.<br /><br />Go ahead,
            check out our website and get what you need!<br />😉👇
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <NewsletterButton link={toolsLink} />
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center bg-[#F0F0F0] py-5">
      <div class="mx-4 sm:w-[580px]">
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-8 text-left">
          <p>
            If you like what you've read, or have any suggestions, let us know
            by filling out this form! 😇<br /><br />Oh, and if you know any
            people or organisations making waves in mental health, tell us! The
            Mental Movement will only work if we work together.<br /><br />Have
            a LIVELY end of week! 🤪 Love you ❤️
          </p>
          <br />
          <p class="font-bold">Stay Sane 😉</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <NewsletterSocialLinks links={newsletterSocialLinks} />
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center bg-slate-50">
      <div class="mx-4 py-6 sm:w-[420px]">
        <p class="text-xs text-[#888888]">
          To make sure you keep getting these emails, please add
          <a href="mailto:hello@howmental.com" class="text-sky-600 underline"
            >hello@howmental.com</a
          > to your address book or allow list. Want out of the loop? <a
            href="/"
            class="text-sky-600 underline">Unsubscribe</a
          >.<br />
          <br />
          18 Sulgrave Road, LONDON, London, Middlesex, W6 7RP, GBR
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <footer role="contentinfo" class="pt-2 pb-8">
    <p class="font-sans">
      Go <a href={newsletterBackPath} class="hover:text-teal underline">back</a>
    </p>
  </footer>
</NewsletterLayout>
